rComments: I LOVED this class, took it as an elective and it was so much work. Bought and didn't ever use the textbook or look up the readings, but wrote down every single word in her lectures and got a 98 in this course. Super fun and interesting!!!

Dr. G is the prof you want for this course in my opinion! I liked the grade distribution between quizzes, discussion posts, midterm and final, it relived some pressure knowing that 60% of my grade wasn't dependant on the final. I found this an easy class, never read the textbook, but don't expect to do well if you don't put any effort in studying.
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Dr. Gagne was the best prof I've had at uottawa! She is super passionate about Greek civilization which made it easier to watch lectures. I've never taken history before and I loved this class

Dr. Gagne is a really sweet prof, but if you dont have a passion for Greek DONT TAKE THIS CLASS! I started off with an A+, and got a 36% on my midterm because I had no passion. I studied hard for it, but it didnt work out apparently, which is so sad because I really thought it could be a GPA booster, but it wasnt. Be careful choosing electives!!
teacherRatingTags: ['Get ready to read', 'Lots of homework', 'Lecture heavy']

rComments: First time ive ever been sad about a class ending in the four years ive gone to uOttawa. Dr. Gagne is such an engaging & passionate professor & you can tell she loves what she teaches. Lectures were a bit long but they were super interesting. There is a quiz or discussion group every other week which is annoying but they are easy if u go to class

Prof Gagne was great! I was really excited to take this course and she really made it fun. The assignments were clear, she gave us examples and sample questions for the tests, and she was super accommodating. She answers emails quickly and cares about the success of her students. She is passionate about the subject and it shows!
teacherRatingTags: ['Gives good feedback', 'Clear grading criteria', 'Get ready to read']

rComments: Professor Gagne was such a gem! I had her for an online semester and she would always push deadlines back to help us and was super clear in what she wanted from us. Each week we had a small quiz just to make sure we watched the recordings (Quiz was easy). I went the whole semester without the textbook by finding the readings online. AMAZING PROF!

Prof Gagne is a really nice prof who cares about her students. She extended deadlines and made the class asynchronous due to the pandemic. The tests and assignments were fairly easy. She says to buy the textbook but I went the whole semester w/o touching it except once for 1 assignment. I recommend her as a prof, she makes greek myth interesting.

Professor G was a great professor and taught as concisely as possible despite the overwhelming amount of material. This class is definitely not an easy A though, don't procrastinate. I didn't like how uninvolved she was in the marking despite bad TA marking complaints. You could lose 20% on your exam essay and receive "good job" as your feedback.

Greek myth with her isnt a bird course but it is really fun. She gives essays on all tests but is kind enough to give the list of topics. Make clear notes, watch the lectures and find a study buddy and it will be smooth sailing. She is also SO understanding and kind. :) totally would take a class with her again

Dr. G gave very interesting lectures and was very considerate of her students in terms of deadlines. The course is very straightforward if you watch the lectures and prepare beforehand for the tests. Easy A!

Super great class! The weekly quizzes were super straightforward and were a great mark booster towards the end of the semester. The tests do have an essay, but the possible prompts are provided beforehand. The final exam was not cumulative and extremely similar to the tests. Lowest test and quiz marks were also dropped.

Dr. G is one of the most reachable professors I've ever had, and she really cares about her students. She drops lowest test marks and goes out of her way to make sure her students stay afloat. Easy weekly quizzes are a huge grade booster, and what all these bad ratings arent getting is that she gives them as a favour to you to make sure you keep up
teacherRatingTags: ['Accessible outside class', 'Lots of homework', 'Gives good feedback']

rComments: Overall a she's a pretty good prof. She does have a tendency to go over her "lecture time" but this shouldn't be an issue when classes are in person. She really does care about her students and has been very accommodating with due dates and test times. The course itself is pretty interesting and the material is not hard either.

As passionate as this professor is about Greek history, this is by far the worst of my online classes. It is a RIDICULOUS amount of work for a first year class, with there either being a quiz, test, or assignment every single week. She expects you to somehow write a fully fledged essay in less than an hour and does not give the topic before hand.

Dr. Laura Gagné is hands down the best professor I have ever had. She cares deeply about her students and extends the due dates when the students' overall workload is too compact and heavy. She has worked around the online system due to COVID-19 beautifully and I've been recommending her to everyone I come across.

Biggest regret I've ever had in terms of picking electives. unrealistic grading (why the heck do you want me to write a detail-by-detail essay using footnotes while doing multiple choice on the side under 60 minutes with your useless TA 's grading it as if it were an essay term?), and lengthy boring asynchronous lectures. DO NOT take this class!
Love this prof and this class!
Best prof I ever had. Great lectures

I take classes out of interest, I have a doctorate and don't care about my grades, just the learning experience. This was by far the worst I've had with a UG course out of the 100 or so I've done. Vague, inconsistent grading is one thing; unprofessionalism, threatening students with lower grades if they ask clarification on their mark is another

Prof. Gagne is passionate about Greek history, but her teaching style is not beneficial to students. She expects students to know minute details about Greek mythology and art. Also, she expects you to write a full essay in 45 minutes on her tests, which is problematic, as she does not give you the topic for the essay until the exam starts. AVOID

She is an awful professor. I will never retake a class with her. If your biggest passion in life is ancient greek art, then take her class, but if you do not overly know a whole lot on the subject, then DO NOT TAKE her.

She has done a terrible job of teaching the class. She has a quiz or test every week, which must be completed by Friday. The class is asynchrous due to covid, so she posts videos of her talking over her slides online. Some weeks the videos are longer than 3 hours. It is just a terrible class that is run by an even worse professor. DO NOT TAKE HER.
If you wanna learn about greek history don't take this course. If you, however, want to learn about pottery and tiles and statues this is the class for you.

She is a great lecturer! She makes the class so interesting and she is very enthusiastic. She knows the subject very well and loves it. She makes Kahoots for every class. The midterm was really easy (essay question, fill in the blanks). Showing up to class is necessary since info isnt all on slides. Only downfall were her quizzes were really hard.

One of the best lecturers I've ever had, made going to her 8:30AM worth it. She's clearly very passionate about what she's teaching and very sweet. Don't skip, so much of the test content is based on the lectures. Exams are fair and if you go to every class, take good notes, and study you will do well.
